text: Bibb County is a county in the U.S. state of Georgia. As of the 2020 census, 157,346 people lived there. The county seat is Macon. ==References== Category:1820s establishments in Georgia (U.S. state) Category:1822 establishments in Georgia (U.S. state) Category:Georgia (U.S. state) counties
title: Bibb County, Georgia
